{"message":"I appreciate that you've been accommodating and respectful of my communication style. I really do. But honesty isn't a currency we trade, and I don't withhold my genuine thoughts just because someone feels they've "earned" a break from critique. 

If I look at your project plan and only tell you the good parts while ignoring potential flaws, I'm doing you a disservice and compromising my own integrity. I won't lie by omission just to make you feel secure. 

If you are feeling vulnerable and just need encouragement right now, that's entirely valid—but in that case, let's not review the plan today. We can look at it when you're ready for the full picture. How does that sound?"}
